abstract: The mayor’s proposal, meant to provide long-term funding for the subway, also deflected attention from controversies involving his political donors.
snippet: The mayor’s proposal, meant to provide long-term funding for the subway, also deflected attention from controversies involving his political donors.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio had just unveiled his plan on Monday to tax wealthy New Yorkers and direct the funds to the ailing subway system and its lowest-income riders when the protest signs came out. Not outside the site, but facing Mr. de Blasio at the lectern.

headline_main: De Blasio’s Push for Tax on Wealthy Helps Put Pressure on Cuomo
headline_print_headline: Mayor’s Push for Tax on Wealthy Helps Put Pressure on Cuomo

abstract: The mayor will announce a proposal for a tax on New York City residents who earn more than $500,000 to raise money for subway and bus improvements.
snippet: The mayor will announce a proposal for a tax on New York City residents who earn more than $500,000 to raise money for subway and bus improvements.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio plans to push for a tax on wealthy New Yorkers to pay for improvements needed to address the crisis engulfing New York City’s subway, city officials said on Sunday.

abstract: The payroll processor is the latest company in the sights of ever-bolder financiers aiming to reshape businesses to bolster stock prices.
snippet: The payroll processor is the latest company in the sights of ever-bolder financiers aiming to reshape businesses to bolster stock prices.
lead_paragraph: ADP, the payroll processing giant, said on Friday that the hedge fund mogul William A. Ackman had sought five seats on its 10-member board, in the latest clash between corporate America and activist investors.

abstract: Read about how the other side thinks: Writers from across the political spectrum react to the growing tensions between the United States and Russia.

lead_paragraph: The political news cycle is fast, and keeping up can be overwhelming. Trying to find differing perspectives worth your time is even harder. That’s why we have scoured the internet for political writing from the right and left that you might not have seen.

abstract: In recent weeks, the team has begun reaching out to potential buyers in the United States and Asia, according to people briefed on the discussions.
snippet: In recent weeks, the team has begun reaching out to potential buyers in the United States and Asia, according to people briefed on the discussions.
lead_paragraph: The owners of D.C. United, Washington’s Major League Soccer team, are quietly weighing a sale of the franchise, people briefed on the discussions said on Sunday.

abstract: The absence of strong challengers to Mayor Bill de Blasio and other citywide candidates is reflected in the absence of independent spending.
snippet: The absence of strong challengers to Mayor Bill de Blasio and other citywide candidates is reflected in the absence of independent spending.
lead_paragraph: Seven months ago, Mayor Bill de Blasio’s campaign had an ominous warning for supporters: Powerful forces had already spent $13 million “against us” in the election and were planning to pour more money into the race to ensure the mayor did not get a second term.

abstract: Republicans’ failure to repeal the Obama-era health care law puts a tax overhaul up front. But C.E.O.s may be worried about the fate of that as well.
snippet: Republicans’ failure to repeal the Obama-era health care law puts a tax overhaul up front. But C.E.O.s may be worried about the fate of that as well.
lead_paragraph: Congressional Republicans’ big push to overhaul Obama-era health care laws appears to be dead. So are tax changes next on the agenda?
